# SkySlope Forms PDF analysis

When improving or debugging SkySlope Forms PDF tooling, treat **filename plus text layer only** as insufficient for scanned or hybrid PDFs.

## What the repo does today

Shared module: `scripts/skyslope-pdf-insight.mjs`

1. **Mozilla pdf.js (legacy build)** in Node — walks each page (up to `SKYSLOPE_PDF_MAX_PAGES`, default 80) for `getTextContent` and `getAnnotations`.
2. **Mandatory OCR** — not optional:
   - If the **whole document** text layer is thin (total extractable characters very low, or every page below the thin threshold), **OCR every page** up to `SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_MAX_PAGES` (default 60).
   - Otherwise **OCR each page** whose extractable text falls below `SKYSLOPE_PDF_THIN_PAGE_CHARS` (default 45 non-whitespace characters), capped by the same max.
3. **OCR engines (per page, first success)**  
   - **Preferred:** Poppler `pdftoppm` + **Tesseract** CLI (higher throughput on a dev machine with Homebrew installs).  
   - **Fallback:** `@napi-rs/canvas` render of the page + **`tesseract.js`** (installed as a devDependency so OCR always runs without system tools).
4. **Merge policy** — on pages that were “thin” before OCR, OCR text **replaces** the weak text layer for downstream SA extraction and vendor scans. On denser pages where OCR is still run as a supplement, OCR is **appended** under an `[OCR]` block.
5. **Annotation inventory** and **e-sign vendor markers** run on the **merged** text.

Principal broker Word brief (`npm run skyslope:forms-brief`) imports this module and surfaces OCR in the **Flags** column and glossary.

## What this does not replace

- **Principal Broker judgment** on whether a form is fully executed under Oregon and office standards.
- **Human review** of initials, counterparties, and firm lines on the authoritative file in SkySlope.

## If you need more than local OCR

- **Full pipeline at scale** (hundreds of long scans): consider Adobe PDF Services, AWS Textract, or batch `ocrmypdf` outside Node, then feed text back in.
- **Higher accuracy** on poor scans: raise `SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_DPI` (default 200, max 300) at the cost of runtime and memory.

## Environment knobs

| Variable | Role |
|----------|------|
| `SKYSLOPE_BRIEF_MAX_PDFS` | How many PDFs the brief analyzes (priority queue). |
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_MAX_PAGES` | Max pages read per PDF for text and annotations. |
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_MAX_PAGES` | Max pages that may receive OCR per file (default 60). |
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_THIN_PAGE_CHARS` | Per-page threshold (non-whitespace chars) for treating a page as image-heavy (default 45). |
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_DPI` | Render scale for the tesseract.js path (default 200, clamped 144 to 300). |
| `SKYSLOPE_MAX_PDF_BYTES` | Download size cap before skipping. |

## Agent behavior

When the user asks for “better PDF reading” or “OCR,” **extend `skyslope-pdf-insight.mjs`** and wire consumers (brief, workbook, comprehensive log, audit) instead of duplicating OCR logic.
